# 🎬 Day 51 - Reels UI (HTML + SCSS + JavaScript)

## 📌 Project Overview

Is project me maine Instagram Reels/TikTok jaisa ek simple Reels UI banaya hai.

Features:

* 📹 Video Reels
* ❤️ Like / Unlike
* 💬 Comment Popup
* 👤 Follow / Unfollow
* 🔄 Dynamic Rendering using JavaScript

---

# 🏗️ HTML Structure

Sabse pehle maine ek container banaya:

```html
<div class="allreel"></div>
```

### `.allreel` kyu banaya?

Ye parent container hai.

Iske andar JavaScript dynamically saari reels insert karta hai.

Structure kuch aisa banta hai:

```
.allreel
    ├── reel
    ├── reel
    ├── reel
    ├── reel
    └── reel
```

Agar `.allreel` nahi hota to saari reels ko ek jagah render karna mushkil hota.

---

# 🎨 SCSS Concepts

Is project me ek important concept use hua hai.

## 1. scroll-snap-type

```scss
scroll-snap-type: y mandatory;
```

### Matlab

Container vertically scroll hoga.

Aur browser force karega ki scroll hamesha next reel par ruk jaye.

Instagram Reels jaisa effect isi se aata hai.

---

## 2. scroll-snap-align

```scss
scroll-snap-align: start;
```

Matlab

Jab reel screen par aaye to uska starting point viewport ke top se align ho.

Har reel perfectly screen me fit hoti hai.

---

## 3. scroll-snap-stop

```scss
scroll-snap-stop: always;
```

Ye browser ko bolta hai:

Fast scroll karo tab bhi ek reel skip mat karna.

Har reel par rukna hi padega.

Isi wajah se scrolling smooth aur controlled lagti hai.

---

# ⚡ JavaScript

## Step 1

Sabse pehle maine reels ka data ek Array me store kiya.

Example:

```js
const reels = [
   {},
   {},
   {}
]
```

Har object ke andar hota hai:

* username
* video
* likes
* comments
* profile image
* caption
* follow status
* like status

Array use karne ka reason:

Ek hi code se unlimited reels bana sakte hain.

---

# Step 2

## showData()

```js
function showData()
```

Ye function poori UI render karta hai.

Har baar jab koi Like kare,
Follow kare,
ya Comment open kare,

tab isi function ko dobara call kiya jata hai.

Isse latest data screen par aa jata hai.

---

# Step 3

## forEach()

```js
reels.forEach((detail,indexnum)=>{
```

Yaha maine `forEach()` use kiya.

### Kyu?

Kyuki mujhe array ki har reel ko ek-ek karke access karna tha.

Har iteration me:

`detail`

Current reel ka object hota hai.

Matlab agar loop dusri reel par hai to `detail` sirf us reel ki information rakhega.

Example:

```
First Loop

detail =
{
 username:"Sunny",
 likes:10
}

Second Loop

detail =
{
 username:"Rahul",
 likes:25
}
```

Har baar detail automatically next object ban jata hai.

Isi wajah se ek hi HTML template baar-baar use karke multiple reels create ho jati hain.

---

# Step 4

## Template Literals

```js
sum += `
<div class="reel">
...
`
```

Yaha template literals use kiye gaye.

Reason:

Dynamic data insert karna easy ho jata hai.

Example:

```js
${detail.username}
```

Ye current reel ka username print karega.

---

# Step 5

## Ternary Operator

```js
detail.isliked
?
'<i class="ri-heart-fill"></i>'
:
'<i class="ri-heart-2-line"></i>'
```

Ye ternary operator hai.

Matlab:

Agar

```
detail.isliked == true
```

to

Filled Heart ❤️

warna

Outline Heart 🤍

Simple language me:

```
Condition ?

True wala

:

False wala
```

Ye if-else ka short form hai.

---

# Step 6

## indexnum

```js
forEach((detail,indexnum)=>{
```

Ye current reel ka index batata hai.

Example:

```
0
1
2
3
4
```

Isi index ko maine HTML me id banakar store kiya.

```html
id="${indexnum}"
```

Baad me isi id ki help se pata chal jata hai kis reel par click hua.

