# Event Delegation

Maine har button par alag Event Listener nahi lagaya.

Sirf ek listener lagaya.

```js
allreel.addEventListener("click",...)
```

Benefit:

* Better Performance
* Kam Code
* Dynamic Elements bhi work karte hain

---

# closest()

Ye project ka naya concept tha.

```js
det.target.closest(".like")
```

Matlab

User ne jis element par click kiya,

uske sabse paas wala parent jiska class `.like` hai usko return karo.

Example

```
i

↓

.like
```

Agar icon par click hua tab bhi `.like` mil jayega.

Isi wajah se event properly kaam karta hai.

---

Comment Open karte waqt bhi yehi concept use hua.

```js
det.target
.closest(".reel")
.querySelector(".comment")
```

Matlab

Jis reel me click hua

usi reel ke andar wala comment box nikaal lo.

Isse dusri reels ke comments affect nahi hote.

---

# Like Logic

Like button click hote hi

pehle check hota hai

```js
isliked
```

Agar

```
false
```

to

```
Like Count++
isliked = true
```

Agar

```
true
```

to

```
Like Count--
isliked = false
```

Uske baad

```js
showData();
```

dobara UI render karta hai.

---

# Follow / Unfollow Logic

Button click hote hi

check hota hai

```js
isFollowed
```

Agar

```
true
```

to

```
false
```

Agar

```
false
```

to

```
true
```

Fir

```js
showData();
```

dobara latest button show karta hai.

---

# Shortcut Logic

Ye pura if-else sirf ek line me bhi likh sakte hain.

```js
reels[index].isFollowed =
!reels[index].isFollowed;
```

`!`

NOT operator hai.

Ye value ko ulta kar deta hai.

```
true

↓

false
```

```
false

↓

true
```

