# 💀 Brutally Honest Review

## Mistakes I Made

* `showData()` ke andar `allreel.innerHTML = sum` loop ke andar hi update ho raha hai. Better practice ye hai ki pehle pura HTML string banao aur loop khatam hone ke baad ek hi baar `innerHTML` update karo.
* Follow logic me `det.target.id` par depend kiya hai. Agar click kisi child element par ho jaye jiske paas `id` na ho, to issue aa sakta hai. `closest()` ka use yaha bhi aur consistent ho sakta tha.
* Comment popup open/close inline styles se control kiya hai. Iski jagah class toggle (`classList.toggle`) use karna code ko aur clean banata.

## Why These Mistakes Happened

Ye mistakes beginner level DOM practice me common hain. Focus feature banane par tha, isliye optimization aur maintainability par kam dhyan gaya.

## Did I Apply Previous Concepts?

Haan. Is project me maine Arrays, Objects, `forEach()`, Template Literals, Event Delegation aur DOM Manipulation ko combine karke use kiya. Sirf syntax yaad nahi rakha, balki concepts ko practical project me apply kiya.

## Before the Next Project

Next project me mujhe ye improve karna hai:

* `classList.add/remove/toggle()` ka zyada use.
* `innerHTML` ko unnecessary baar-baar update na karna.
* Functions ko chhote reusable parts me divide karna.
* Event Delegation aur `closest()` ko aur confidently use karna.
* State aur UI rendering ko aur clean structure me organize karna.

Overall, ye project sirf DOM manipulation nahi, balki data aur UI ko connect karne ki direction me ek strong step tha.
